Package core

Interface HlaExecutionConfiguration

  • All Superinterfaces:
    HlaExecutionConfigurationAttributes, HlaHLAobjectRootAttributes, HlaObjectInstanceBase
    public interface HlaExecutionConfiguration
extends HlaExecutionConfigurationAttributes, HlaObjectInstanceBase
    Interface used to represent an object instance.

    This class is ThreadSafe as defined by Java Concurrency in Practice, see jcip.net.

      • addHlaExecutionConfigurationListener

        void addHlaExecutionConfigurationListener​(HlaExecutionConfigurationListener listener)
        Adds a listener. The listener is notified when any attribute of this object is updated. This listener is also called when an interaction is sent to this object. This method is idempotent. To make sure that no attribute updates arrive before adding the listener, use: HlaExecutionConfigurationManager.addHlaExecutionConfigurationDefaultInstanceListener(HlaExecutionConfigurationListener listener).
        Parameters:
        listener - The listener to add.

      • removeHlaExecutionConfigurationListener

        void removeHlaExecutionConfigurationListener​(HlaExecutionConfigurationListener listener)
        Removes a listener. This method is idempotent. Trying to remove a non-registered listener is equivalent to a no-op.
        Parameters:
        listener - The listener to remove.

      • addHlaExecutionConfigurationValueListener

        void addHlaExecutionConfigurationValueListener​(HlaExecutionConfigurationValueListener valueListener)
        Adds a valueListener. The valueListener is notified when any attribute of this object is updated. Note that the attribute values that are notified are not guaranteed to be the latest available values for that attribute. This method is idempotent. To make sure that no attribute updates arrive before adding the listener, use: HlaExecutionConfigurationManager.addHlaExecutionConfigurationDefaultInstanceValueListener(HlaExecutionConfigurationValueListener valueListener).
        Parameters:
        valueListener - The valueListener to add.
